ing Fund\">Access to Learning Fund</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Your course</h2>\n\n<p>Your course must be in the UK and one of the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a first degree, eg BA, BSc or BEd</li>\n  <li>a Foundation Degree </li>\n  <li>a Certificate of Higher Education </li>\n  <li>a Diploma of Higher Education (DipHE)</li>\n  <li>a Higher National Certificate (HNC) </li>\n  <li>a Higher National Diploma (HND) </li>\n  <li>a Postgraduate Certificate of Education (PGCE) </li>\n  <li>Initial Teacher Training </li>\n  <li>further training of youth and community workers </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Check with your university or college that your course is recognised.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Part-time course intensity</h2>\n\n<p>For part-time students, your course intensity can affect how much you get. Intensity means how long your course takes to complete each year compared to an equivalent full-time course. </p>\n\n<p>Part-time courses starting <strong>from</strong> 1 September 2012 must: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>last at least 1 year</li>\n  <li>not last more than 4 times as long as the equivalent full-time course </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Part-time courses starting <strong>before</strong> 1 September 2012 must not last more than twice as long as the equivalent full-time course.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can check course intensity with your university or college.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/disabled-students-allowances-dsas/how-to-claim","slug":"how-to-claim","order":4,"title":"How to apply","body":"<p>To apply for Disabled Students&rsquo; Allowances (<abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr>) send form DSA1 to Student Finance England.  </p>\n\n<h2>Application form</h2>\n\n<p>If you’ve applied for student finance use version &lsquo;DSA1 short&rsquo;. If you’re only applying for <abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr> use version &lsquo;DSA1 full&rsquo;.</p>\n