 National Scholarship Programme</h2>\n\n<p>You can apply for a bursary from the National Scholarship Programme if your household income is £25,000 a year or less </p>\n\n<p>The bursary can be one or more of the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a cash bursary of up to £1,000</li>\n  <li>help with tuition fees and accommodation </li>\n  <li>a free foundation year (a programme that helps students meet the entry criteria for a higher education course)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re awarded a cash bursary it&rsquo;s paid directly into your bank account by your university or college.</p>\n\n<p>Contact your university or college to find out how and when to apply.</p>\n\n<h2>Leaving local authority care</h2>\n\n<p>If you’ve been in local authority care, you can apply for: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a one-off bursary of £2,000 from your local authority  </li>\n  <li>a bursary from your university or college  </li>\n</ul>\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Student finance, loans and universities","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/education%2Fstudent-finance.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Including loans, bursaries, grants, student finance and paying back loans","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=education%2Fstudent-finance","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/education/student-finance"},"parent":{"title":"Education and learning","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/education.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Get help if you&#39;re at school, planning to go on to further or higher education, looking for training or interested in a student or career development loan.","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=education","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/education"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/student-finance-calculator.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/student-finance-calcula