ner&rsquo;s, plus your own). The grant is paid directly to your university or college.</p>\n\n<p>You must study at a rate of at least 50% equivalent to a full-time course (check with your university or college).</p>\n\n<p>Full-time students can’t apply.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Part-time student household income</th>\n      <th>Fee Grant</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Up to £16,845</td>\n      <td>£820 to £1,230</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£16,846 to £25,420</td>\n      <td>£770 to £1,180</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Over £25,420</td>\n      <td>No grant</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Maintenance Loan for living costs</h2>\n\n<p>You must be a full-time UK student.</p>\n\n<p>You have to pay the loan back. The loan depends on your household income (parents’ or partner’s income plus yours) and where you live. It will be paid into your bank account at the start of term.</p>\n\n<p>You can’t apply if you’re a part-time or an <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> student </p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Full-time student</th>\n      <th>Maintenance Loan per year</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Living at home</td>\n      <td>Up to £3,838</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Living away from home, outside London</td>\n      <td>Up to £4,950</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Living away from home, in London</td>\n      <td>Up to £6,928</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Maintenance Grant for living costs</h2>\n\n<p>You must be a full-time UK student.</p>\n\n<p>You don’t have to pay the grant back - the grant depends on your household income (parents’ or partner’s income plus yours) and when you start your course.</p>\n\n<p>The grant is paid into your bank account at the start of term.</p>\n\n<p>You can’t apply if you’re a part-time or an <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> student.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Full-time student – household income</th>\n      <th>Maintenance Grant per year</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£25,000 or less</td>\n      <td>£2,984</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£25,001- £50,695</td>\n      <td>£50 to £2,983</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Over £50,695</td>\n      <td>No grant</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Course Grant for living costs</h2>\n\n<p>You can apply if you&rsquo;re a part-time UK or <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> students.</p>\n\n<p>The grant depends on your household income (your parents’ or partner’s plus yours).</p>\n\n<p>The grant is paid directly into your account at the start of term.</p>\n\n<p>Full-time students can’t apply.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Part-time student household income</th>\n      <th>Course Grant per year</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>up to £26,029</td>\n      <td>£265</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£26,030 to £28,065</td>\n      <td>£50 to £264</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Over £28,065</td>\n      <td>No grant</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Extra help</h2>\n<p>You might also be able to get: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/extra-money-pay-university\" title=\"scholarships and bursaries\">scholarships and bursaries</a>  from your college or university, eg if you&rsquo;re on a low income</li>\n  <li>extra help for students with children: a <a href=\"/childcare-grant\" title=\"Childcare Grant\">Childcare Grant</a> or a <a href=\"/parents-learning-allowance\" title=\"parents' learning allowance\">Parents&rsquo; Learning Allowance</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/disabled-students-allowances-dsas\" title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">Disabled Students&rsquo; Allowances</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"nhs-bursaries\" title=\"NHS bursaries\">NHS bursaries</a> for medical students </li>\n  <li><a href=\"/social-work-bursaries\" title=\"social work bursaries\">Social work bursaries</a> </li>\n  <li><a href=\"/access-to-learning-fund\" title=\"Access to Learning Fund\">Access to Learning Fund</a> if you&rsquo;re on a low income</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Repayments</h2>\n<p>Your payments are linked to your income. You only make repayments when your income is over £15,795 a year.</p>\n\n<p>Each month you pay back 9% of any income over £15,795.</p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong> </p>\n\n<p>You earn £18,000. This is £2,205 over the £15,795 threshold.</p>\n\n<p>You repay 9% of £2,205 = £198 per year, or £16 per month</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The Student Loans Company has <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.studentloanrepayment.co.uk/portal/page?_pageid=93,6678408&amp;_dad=portal&amp;_schema=PORTAL#tab2\" title=\"detailed information on student finance repayments\">detailed information on repayments.</a></p>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Student finance, loans and universities","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/education%2Fstudent-finance.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Including loans, bursaries, grants, student finance and paying back loans","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=education%2Fstudent-finance","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/education/student-finance"},"parent":{"title":"Education and learning","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/education.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Get help if you&#39;re at school, planning to go on to further or higher education, looking for training or interested in a student or career development loan.","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=education","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/education"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/extra-money-pay-university.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/extra-money-pay-university","title":"Extra money to pay for university","format":"answer","updated_at