plication as evidence of income. If more details are needed Student Finance England will contact you.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Depending on your circumstances you may also need to give evidence of:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>divorce or separation</li>\n  <li>dependent children</li>\n  <li>outgoings</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Earned income</h3>\n\n<p>If you’re supporting a 2012 to 2013 application you need to give financial details for the 2010 to 2011 tax year.</p>\n\n<p>If Student Finance England can&rsquo;t work out your income using your National Insurance number you may need to send photocopies of your:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>P60</li>\n  <li>pay slips</li>\n  <li>tax return</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you expect your income to drop by 15% or more, you can ask to be assessed on the current tax year. You&rsquo;ll need to complete an income assessment form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sfengland.slc.co.uk/media/393127/cyi.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Current year income assessment form for 2012 to 2013' (PDF, 85KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Current year income assessment form for 2012 to 2013’ (PDF, 85KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Unearned income</h3>\n\n<p>You need to give evidence of any unearned income from the prior tax year (2010 to 2011 for 2012 to 2013 applications).</p>\n\n<p>Unearned income includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>interest from savings</li>\n  <li>benefits</li>\n  <li>pensions</li>\n  <li>rent from property or a room</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Evidence of unearned income can include photocopies of:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Self Assessment tax return</li>\n  <li>statements showing interest or investments</li>\n  <li>income details from an accountant</li>\n  <li>pension book or letter</li>\n  <li>P60s</li>\n  <li>benefit book</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>If you’re divorced or separated</h3>\n\n<p>If you’re divorced or separated you need to give a photocopy of one of the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>divorce - Decree Nisi, Decree Absolute</li>\n  <li>dissolution of a civil partnership - civil partnership dissolution order</li>\n  <li>confirmation from a solicitor of your marital status</li>\n  <li>Council Tax bill showing the 25% discount for single occupancy (as evidence that you&rsquo;re now separated)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re married or living with a partner you don’t need to send evidence of this.</p>\n\n<h3>Dependent children</h3>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t need to send evidence of dependent children but you should mention this in your online application. </p>\n\n<h2>Where to send your evidence</h2>\n\n<p>Send your evidence to Student Finance England.</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\n\n<br />Student Finance England \n<br />PO Box 210 \n<br />Darlington \n<br />DL1 9HJ\n<br />\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Student finance, loans and universities","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/education%2Fstudent-finance.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Including loans, bursaries, grants, student finance and paying back loans","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=education%2Fstudent-finance","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/education/student-finance"},"parent":{"title":"Education and learning","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/education.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Get help if you&#39;re at school, planning to go on to further or higher education, looking for training or interested in a student or career development loan.","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=education","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/education"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Directgov","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/directgov.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":null,"short_description":null,"type":"legacy_source"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=directgov","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/b